cl-opengl is a set of idiomatic [[CFFI]] bindings for the OpenGL API.

== Tutorials ==

* Patrick Stein has a good selection of NeHe tutorial ports:
** [http://nklein.com/2010/06/nehe-tutorials-for-cl-opengl/ Tutorial 1] - Setup cl-opengl.
** [http://nklein.com/2010/06/nehe-tutorial-02-drawing-triangles-and-quadrilaterals/ Tutorial 2] - Drawing triangles and quadrilaterals.
** [http://nklein.com/2010/06/nehe-tutorial-03-color/ Tutorial 3] - Bright and beautiful (Adding colour).
** [http://nklein.com/2010/06/nehe-tutorial-04-rotation/ Tutorial 4] - Putting a new spin on it (Rotation)
** [http://nklein.com/2010/06/nehe-tutorial-05-solids/ Tutorial 5] - Adding some meat (Solids)
** [http://nklein.com/2010/06/nehe-tutorial-06-textured-solids/ Tutorial 6] - Pretty Picture (Textured solids)

* 3b's Tutorial series:
